net.imglib2.cache

Class IoSync<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.imglib2.cache.IoSync<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - key type
    V - value type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    CacheLoader<K,V>, CacheRemover<K,V>

    public class IoSync<K,V>
extends Object
implements CacheLoader<K,V>, CacheRemover<K,V>
    Handle concurrent loading and saving of cache entries. It can be used directly as a CacheRemover and CacheLoader. The onRemoval(Object, Object) method enqueues values for writing and returns immediately. Actual writing is done asynchronously on separate threads, calling the connected CacheRemover.

    IoSync takes care of directly returning values that reloaded are while they are written. It ensures that the final state of a value that is enqueued for removal several times is the state that is written (eventually).

    A crucial assumption is that only one thread calls get get(Object) onRemoval(Object, Object) with the same key simultaneously. The current SoftRefLoaderRemoverCache implementation guarantees that. The same is guaranteed to the connected CacheRemover and CacheLoader.

    TODO: If we want to avoid ever having corrupt data on disk, then get() should block while existing value is written, i.e., synchronize both Writer and get() on entry. Otherwise the value currently being written is returned and potentially modified. If we don't care about corrupt disk data, only consistency of data in memory, then this is not a problem.

    Author:
    Tobias Pietzsch

    • Constructor Detail

      • IoSync

        public IoSync(T io)
        Create a new IoSync that asynchronously forwards to the specified CacheRemover. Uses 1 writer thread and a bounded write queue of size 10.
        Parameters:
        io - used to asynchronously write removed values, and to load values that are not currently enqueued for writing.

      • IoSync

        public IoSync(T io,
              int numThreads,
              int maxQueueSize)
        Create a new IoSync that asynchronously forwards to the specified CacheRemover. The specified number of IoSync.Writer threads is started to handle writing values through saver. New writer threads can be always started later, for example by new Thread(iosync.new Writer()).start().
        Parameters:
        io - used to asynchronously write removed values, and to load values that are not currently enqueued for writing.
        numThreads - how many writer threads to start (may be 0).
        maxQueueSize - the maximum size of the write queue. When the queue is full, CacheRemover.onRemoval(Object, Object) will block until earlier values have been written.

      • IoSync

        Create a new IoSync that asynchronously forwards to the specified CacheRemover. The specified number of IoSync.Writer threads is started to handle writing values through saver. New writer threads can be always started later, for example by new Thread(iosync.new Writer()).start().
        Parameters:
        loader - used to load values that are not currently enqueued for writing.
